RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIFORNIA BAY bumped leaving the gate, settled off the pace and moved inside, ridden along through the far turn, swung out leaving the bend, reached the front with a furlong remaining and kicked clear to win going away under mild asking. SILVER N BLACK bobbled leaving the gate, chased two wide into the first turn then became rank around the bend, bid three deep on the far turn and vied for command into the stretch, took over briefly in upper stretch before being passed by the winner and stayed on to hold second. SILENT HEAT had to steady briefly behind SILVER N BLACK on the first turn, raced outside a rival in mid-pack up the backstretch, took closer order into the far turn, lacked room past the quarter pole and bumped with outer rival into the stretch, lacked room behind the leaders again entering the final furlong, altered out midstretch and finished determinedly to miss second. GHOSTLY ACT set the pace from inside under pressure, carried a short lead over outer rival around the far turn, vied with a pair of foes into the lane, relinquished the lead in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. BRONKO NAGURSKI settled inside, chased under coaxing into the far turn, found traffic behind the leader exiting the far turn, remained behind GHOSTLY ACT in the lane before altering to a clear path but could not find the needed late response. TITOS WITH A TWIST threw his head and bumped leaving the gate, trailed early from inside, remained along the fence to the far turn, eased off the rail around that bend and failed to menace. JOHNNY PAYCHECK prompted the pace from outside in the two path, kept the pressure on through the far turn, vied between past the quarter pole, bumped into the lane and steadied shortly after, then weakened down the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Johnny Paycheck
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, bumped/steadied into str, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Titos With a Twist
ENTRY.OWNER: Helm Racing Stable and Strauss William
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head/bumped start, inside, moved out, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: California Bay
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, settled inside, swung out, going away, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Silent Heat
ENTRY.OWNER: Newfield Farm and Johnson Peter O
ENTRY.COMMENT: brief steady 1st, 2wide, lacked room/bumped 3/16, traffic str

ENTRY.NAME: Silver N Black
ENTRY.OWNER: White Fence LLC Buckendorf Larry S and Underhill Peter G
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled bit, rank 1st, bid 3deep, led upper, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 94. Claiming Purse 31000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELLA RENELLA dueled for the lead from inside, fought through the turn and into the lane, inched ahead in upper stretch before clearing at the eighth pole, then drew off under right-handed urging. INDY'S STAR dueled for the lead outside BELLA RENELLA, inched head on the turn, overtaken by the winner in upper stretch, could not keep up with that rival approaching the final furlong but kept on to secure the place. SHEZA GIRLY GIRL chased outside a rival into the turn, traveled two wide around the bend, angled out past the quarter pole and came four wide into the lane, churned on through the lane while moving out further and edged FLAT OUT JOY for the show. FLAT OUT JOY was off slow to begin, went up to stalk the top pair from outside, chased three wide through the turn, drifted when asked left-handed and and failed to respond to urging while getting outfinished for third. HENNYS CRAZY TRAIN tracked from inside out of range, lost ground on the rail through the turn and weakened. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, BELLA RENELLA HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Bella Renella
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC Medina Lizbeth and Pineda Milton

ENTRY.NAME: Sheza Girly Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: Davis Racing LLC Giordano Louis A and Mueller Martin

ENTRY.NAME: Flat Out Joy
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, stalked outside, 3wide, no response

ENTRY.NAME: Indy's Star
ENTRY.OWNER: A and J Racing and R and K Racing

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Brandywine Farm (Jim & Pam Robinson) & Parker Place Breedi

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 108. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Maiden And Cla iming Races For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANTASTIC unhurried in the two path outside a rival at the back early, took closer around the far turn and set his sights on the top pair into the stretch, moved out to commence a bid three deep and proved best late. CANE CREEK ROAD cleared and crossed over to the inside, showed the way to the far turn, challenged with a quarter mile left to run, dueled through the lane and yielded grudgingly late. TIME TO PARTY rated in the two path early, moved up to be closest in pursuit on the far turn, challenged past the quarter pole, dueled head to head then between foes late and got outkicked. SPIRIT MAKER was antsy in the starting gate, bobbled in the beginning, became rank into and early on the first turn, settled on the inside, moved closer around the second bend, tipped out at the top of the lane and finished willingly for a minor award. REDLINE stalked the pace on the inside through both turns and lacked a bid when called upon.

ENTRY.NAME: Time to Party
ENTRY.OWNER: David A Bernsen LLC and Weijland Holdings LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated 2wide, bid outside 1/4, dueled str, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Spirit Maker
ENTRY.COMMENT: antsy, bobbled, rank early, settled inside, tipped out, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Vantastic
ENTRY.OWNER: Ciaglia Racing LLC and SAF Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Cane Creek Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared, crossed over, pace inside, dueled, grudgingly

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUCK OWENS tracked outside a rival four wide into the turn, asked three wide late on the bend, drew alongside the leaders midstretch, took over at the sixteenth pole and drove clear. STAN FROM MALIBU pressed the pace from outside, raced on even terms midway around the bend, took over in upper stretch but got outkicked by the winner in deep stretch. TOM HORN set the pace with STAN FROM MALIBU to the outside, headed midway around the turn, dueled into the lane, lost command in upper stretch, fought on to the sixteenth pole then faltered late. MONTANA stalked the top pair up the backstretch, asked two wide on the turn, angled inside in upper stretch and weakened. REEF CITY sat off the pace early on, took the turn two then three wide and failed to menace. COUNTRY BOY was off a bit slow from outside, trailed outside a rival early, rounded the bend four wide, moved inward at the top of the lane and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, For Each $6,250 To $50,000 1 lb. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREE AND HUMBLE settled on the inside, angled four wide around the bend, reached the front in midstretch under hand urging and drew away late. AVA'S STORM showed early speed then cleared inner rivals and crossed over, set all the pace to the stretch, challenged from the winner entering the final furlong, relinquished the lead midstretch and stayed on to save the place. ENCOLPION had early speed inside a pair of rivals then got brushed crossing back on to the turn, pulled briefly at the seven-sixteenths pole then steadied at the half-mile pole, stalked the pace while hugging the rail to the stretch, tipped out in the lane and gained the show. MISS POLO BAR tracked outside a rival then three deep into the turn, remained three wide into the lane, chased within striking distance into the final furlong but lacked the needed late punch. UNKEPT SECRET trailed on the inside into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the lane and passed tired rivals. LA PALOMA BLANCA stalked off the rail then between foes into the turn, got boxed in around the bend losing ground, tipped out in upper stretch and weakened in the final furlong. TURQUOISE BIKINI got floated in crossing the dirt and brushed with rival early, was closest in pursuit two wide on the turn and into the lane weakened in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Han Moon S and Pineda Milton G

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARLOTTE HARBOR reserved in the early going, patiently handled wo wide or between foes on the turn, angled four wide into the lane, drew alongside SOUL SWEET with a sixteenth remaining and drove past. SOUL SWEET chased briefly then went up to challenge SPOILED ROTTEN from outside, kept the pressure on through the turn and raced on even terms leaving the bend, took over into the stretch, put away inner rival midstretch but was outkicked by the winner in the late stages. SPOILED ROTTEN took control early from inside then dueled with SOUL SWEET up the backstretch, inched ahead on the turn, lost command leaving the bend, fought to midstretch and flattened in the final sixteenth. EVERLYS GIRL bumped inner rival at the start, raced up close three deep then chased the top pair leaving the backstretch, took aim three wide into the lane but flattened in the furlong grounds. ROMAN EMPRESS was a touch rank chasing early before stalking on the inside, saved ground to the stretch and failed to rally. ROSES R BLUE got bumped back leaving the gate, moved up to be forwardly placed four deep outside the leaders then chased into the turn, spun five wide into the lane and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 6 1/2F Turf CR: 96. Starter Allowance Purse 38000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REAL FIRE broke well but was taken back, trailed up the backstretch, went two wide into the turn, angled out while advancing outside rivals and came five wide into the stretch, reached the front midstretch and drove clear. M IS FOR MAGIC settled outside a rival, found traffic behind foes on the bend while two then three wide, lacked room again in upper stretch, tipped out to a clear path and finished willingly for the place. SHE'S GOT A WAY stalked in the two path outside a rival into the turn, chased between foes around the bend, tipped out and bid three wide at the top of the lane, took over briefly with a furlong remaining, was soon passed midstretch and lost the place. TEEN DRAMA dueled for command from inside, clung to a narrow lead in upper stretch, relinquished the lead at the eighth pole and flattened to fourth. PALEO'S PRINCESS settled on the inside, tipped two wide into the lane, lacked room in upper stretch, moved out then back in only to lack room again at the sixteenth pole and could never build up any momentum. PROFESSORS' PRIDE stumbled outward to bump rival, showed speed and went up to duel from outside, fought into and around the turn and into the lane but weakened in the furlong grounds. ICE QUEEN stalked on the inside entering the turn, waited past the five-sixteenths pole and into the lane, continued behind rivals on the inside through the lane and never gained a clear path. GRITTY GIRL took a bump from inner rival at the start, stalked three deep into the turn, chased four wide into the lane and came up empty.

FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY MAN BAGS raced up close outside the dueling pair, challenged three deep on the turn before moving clear at the quarter pole, was hand urged through the lane and held safely to the wire. ESTABLISHED stalked two wide into the turn, tipped out and was roused three deep with a quarter mile remaining, chased the winner through the final furlong but had to settle for second best. CHASING FAME moved off the inside while tracking at the back, went four wide around the turn then three wide into the lane, could not threaten the top pair but was a clear third. GOLD CRUSHER was a bit fractious in the gate, bobbled at the start, sent to duel from inside, vied with rivals on the turn, could not keep up approaching the quarter pole and tired in the lane. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIRTH OF COOL trailed on the inside early, remained at the back into the lane, looked to rally but got caught in traffic in upper stretch, tipped out to a clear path, surged late and proved best in the end. GOLDENEYE pulled chasing along the fence early then settled in a stalking position, coaxed into the far turn, lacked room behind the leader from the quarter pole to the top of the stretch, tipped out in the lane and gained command at the sixteenth pole but could not offer any resistance to the winner late. TALLIS was off slow in the beginning, reserved early in the two path, raced near the inside then two wide on the far turn, moved out and launched a bid three deep midstretch but lacked the needed late kick in the final sixteenth. THIRTY FOUR COUPE dueled for command from inside, inched ahead to take control, cleared into the far turn, challenged again into the lane, put away that challenger for good in upper stretch, showed the way into the final furlong but yielded in deep stretch. SO I'M TOLD stumbled leaving the gate, stalked between foes in the two path, spun three wide into the drive, bothered a bit past the eighth pole and flattened. KEEN TO GO bumped with outer rival at the start, stalked three deep early, remained outside rivals and came four wide into the lane and weakened in the drive. OVERRULE dueled for command from outside early, pressed up the backstretch, lost touch with the leader into the far turn, chased two wide around the bend, re-engaged THIRTY FOUR COUPE entering the stretch but weakened in the drive. DERECHO DANDY bumped with KEEN TO GO in the beginning, stalked four deep around the clubhouse turn, chased three, four, then five wide into the lane, drifted in slightly in upper stretch and weakened.
